import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['group'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['group'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['group'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Median')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of group sizes?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['group'] = pd.to_numeric(data['group'], errors='coerce')
    avg_group_size = data['group'].mean()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.bar('Average Group Size', avg_group_size, color='blue')
    ax.axhline(avg_group_size, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Group Size: {avg_group_size:.2f}')
    ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average group size?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['count'] = data.groupby('group')['person'].transform('count')
    plt.hist(data['count'], bins=range(0, max(data['count'])+2, 1), edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['count'].mean(), color='red', label='Mean: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].mean()))
    plt.xlabel('People per group')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of people per group?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['group'].value_counts().plot(kind='bar')
    plt.title('What is the most common group size?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Group size')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('group')['person'].apply(list).reset_index(name='people')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))
    ax.boxplot(data['people'], vert=False)
    ax.set_xlabel('People')
    ax.set_ylabel('Group')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of people across groups?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
